@startuml "Orchestrators - Workflow Coordination"
title "Orchestrators: Workflow Coordination and State Management"

' Main Terminal Entry Point
class InfrawareTerminal {
  - state: TerminalState
  - event_handler: EventHandler
  - input_classifier: InputClassifier
  - command_orchestrator: CommandOrchestrator
  - nl_orchestrator: NaturalLanguageOrchestrator
  - tab_completion: TabCompletionHandler
  --
  + new(): Self
  + run(): Result<()>
  + handle_event(event): Result<()>
  + render()
}

package "Orchestrators" {
  class CommandOrchestrator {
    - executor: CommandExecutor
    --
    + execute_command(cmd, args): Result<String>
    + check_install_available(cmd): bool
    + prompt_install(cmd): Result<bool>
  }

  class NaturalLanguageOrchestrator {
    - llm_client: Box<dyn LLMClientTrait>
    - renderer: ResponseRenderer
    --
    + query_llm(text: &str): Result<String>
    + render_response(response: &str): String
    + format_markdown(md: &str): String
  }

  class TabCompletionHandler {
    - command_executor: CommandExecutor
    - tab_completion: TabCompletion
    --
    + get_completions(input, cursor_pos): Vec<String>
    + complete_command(prefix): Vec<String>
    + complete_file(prefix): Vec<String>
  }
}

note top of CommandOrchestrator
  **Single Responsibility**
  Handles command execution workflow:
  1. Classify input as command
  2. Check if command exists
  3. Execute command
  4. Handle installation prompt (M2/M3)
  5. Return result to terminal

  **Error Handling**
  - Command not found -> suggest install
  - Execution error -> display error
  - Timeout -> notify user
end note

note top of NaturalLanguageOrchestrator
  **Single Responsibility**
  Handles natural language workflow:
  1. Classify input as NL
  2. Query LLM backend
  3. Format markdown response
  4. Apply syntax highlighting
  5. Display to user

  **Response Rendering**
  - Code blocks with syntax highlight
  - Inline formatting (bold, italic)
  - Markdown to ANSI conversion
end note

note top of TabCompletionHandler
  **Single Responsibility**
  Handles tab completion workflow:
  1. Analyze input prefix
  2. Determine completion type:
     - Commands (binary path lookup)
     - Files (filesystem scan)
     - Flags (per-command)
  3. Return matching suggestions
  4. Handle selection
end note

' State Management
class TerminalState {
  + output: OutputBuffer
  + input: InputBuffer
  + history: CommandHistory
  + mode: TerminalMode
  --
  + add_output(line): void
  + submit_input(): String
  + clear_input(): void
}

enum TerminalMode {
  Normal
  ExecutingCommand
  WaitingLLM
  PromptingInstall
}

class OutputBuffer {
  - lines: Vec<String>
  - scroll_offset: usize
  - max_lines: usize = 10000
  --
  + add_line(line): void
  + add_lines(lines): void
  + scroll_up(): void
  + scroll_down(): void
  + clear(): void
}

class InputBuffer {
  - text: String
  - cursor_pos: usize
  --
  + insert_char(c): void
  + delete_char(): void
  + move_cursor_left(): void
  + move_cursor_right(): void
  + set_text(text): void
  + take(): String
}

class CommandHistory {
  - entries: Vec<String>
  - position: Option<usize>
  --
  + add(cmd): void
  + previous(): Option<String>
  + next(): Option<String>
  + reset_position(): void
}

note right of TerminalState
  **Composition over Inheritance**
  Terminal state composed of:
  - OutputBuffer (scrollable output)
  - InputBuffer (text with cursor)
  - CommandHistory (navigation)
  - TerminalMode (current state)

  **Single Responsibility**
  Each buffer handles its domain:
  - OutputBuffer: display, trimming
  - InputBuffer: editing, cursor
  - CommandHistory: navigation
end note

TerminalState --> OutputBuffer : contains
TerminalState --> InputBuffer : contains
TerminalState --> CommandHistory : contains
TerminalState --> TerminalMode : tracks

' TUI Rendering
class TerminalTUI {
  - terminal: Terminal
  - frame: Frame
  --
  + render(state: &TerminalState): Result<()>
  + render_output(area: Rect): void
  + render_input(area: Rect): void
  + render_status(area: Rect): void
}

class EventHandler {
  + poll_event(timeout): Result<Option<TerminalEvent>>
  - handle_keyboard(key): TerminalEvent
  - handle_mouse(mouse): TerminalEvent
}

enum TerminalEvent {
  KeyPressed { key: KeyCode, modifiers: KeyModifiers }
  MouseEvent { button, x, y }
  Resize { width, height }
  Paste { text }
}

note right of TerminalTUI
  **TUI Rendering Layer**
  Uses ratatui framework:
  - Terminal layout (output, input, status)
  - Real-time updates
  - Event-driven rendering
  - Cross-platform support
end note

' Workflow Integration
package "Main Event Loop Flow" {
  rectangle "Poll Event" as e1
  rectangle "Classify Input" as e2
  rectangle "Route to Handler" as e3
  rectangle "Command Path" as cmd_path
  rectangle "NL Path" as nl_path
  rectangle "Update State" as e4
  rectangle "Render" as e5

  e1 --> e2
  e2 --> e3
  e3 -->|Command| cmd_path
  e3 -->|NaturalLanguage| nl_path
  e3 -->|CommandTypo| cmd_path
  e3 -->|Empty| e4
  cmd_path --> e4
  nl_path --> e4
  e4 --> e5
}

InfrawareTerminal --> TerminalState : manages
InfrawareTerminal --> EventHandler : polls
InfrawareTerminal --> InputClassifier : uses
InfrawareTerminal --> CommandOrchestrator : routes commands
InfrawareTerminal --> NaturalLanguageOrchestrator : routes NL
InfrawareTerminal --> TerminalTUI : renders
InfrawareTerminal --> TabCompletionHandler : handles completion

CommandOrchestrator --> TerminalState : updates
NaturalLanguageOrchestrator --> TerminalState : updates
TabCompletionHandler --> TerminalState : updates

EventHandler --> TerminalEvent : returns
TerminalTUI --> TerminalState : reads

' Design notes
note bottom
  **Architecture Principles**

  1. **Separation of Concerns**
     - Orchestrators handle workflows
     - State manages data
     - TUI handles rendering
     - Handlers classify input

  2. **Single Responsibility**
     - Each orchestrator has one purpose
     - Each buffer component is focused
     - CommandExecutor only executes
     - InputClassifier only classifies

  3. **Dependency Injection**
     - Orchestrators receive dependencies
     - No hard-coded globals (except cache)
     - Testable and mockable

  4. **Event-Driven**
     - Main loop: poll -> process -> render
     - Non-blocking operations
     - Async execution with tokio
     - Responsive UI
end note

@enduml
